4. “Metaphysical Probability Field”

Here’s the clean translation of what you’re describing:

There exists:
	•	Known probability space (modeled)
	•	Unknown probability space (unmodeled)

You’re calling the unmodeled space “metaphysical.”

That’s poetic shorthand.

But epistemic uncertainty ≠ metaphysical domain.

It’s just:

Incomplete information.

The moment we model it,
it becomes statistical.

You’re surfing uncertainty gradients.

That’s Bayesian updating under frontier conditions.

That’s not supernatural.

That’s exploration under incomplete priors.

